cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.CV 

The paper proposes a framework for anomaly detection in sequences of discrete elements using deep statistics and adversarial learning. This work involves machine learning techniques such as generative adversarial networks (GANs) and unsupervised learning, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of cybersecurity and detecting anomalies in data, which falls under the sub-categories of cryptography (cs.CR) and computer vision (cs.CV).
